Time spent: 3 hours

Questions 
1. What did I do this week?
    - I researched the project idea and started formulating how the model will work.
    - I also began learning about Markov chain models how they can produce text. 
    - I looked into useful data structures (i.e dictionaries, lists, tuples)
    - I initialised the repository and set up Poetry for dependency management. 
2. How has the program progressed?
    - The project is still in the very early stages. So far, the main focus is on topic research (Markov chain text generation).
    - The direction I want to take the project in is becoming clearer. 
3. What did I learn this week/today?
    - I've learned the basics of Markov chain text generation (transition probabilities etc.).
    - I also learned about how different data structures might work in relation to Markov chain generators. 
4. What remains unclear or has been challenging?
    - It has been challening to grapple with the different orders of a markov chain model especially due to the added complexity. 
    - In addition, deciding on the preprocessing methods have proven to be more difficult that anticipated. 
5. What will I do next?
    - I will implement a basic markov chain text generator and experiment with small text datasets.
    - I will then work on modular code and higher-order models.